<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/09-Forward Thinking</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/09-Forward Thinking</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By John Koten<p>Clint Willis's cover story for this issue, "Going Small," offers a number of stock recommendations. Readers tell us that they like this kind of piece -- some because they enjoy seeing the process of stock picking explained in detail and others because they are simply eager for good tips.<p>But there's always the issue of timing. Some readers get angry when the price of a stock has changed since our publication date. This happened with Clint's last piece,  "Finding the Next <a name="NASD:MSFT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14120"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Microsoft</b></a>," published in our June issue.<p>We shipped this story to the printer on April 10, updating the stock prices at the last moment. Printing was completed on April 26, and the issue was mailed on April 30. Subscribers began receiving their issues as early as May 1. Newsstand buyers, however, waited two more weeks. (Not our preference: Newsstands won't put monthly magazines on the shelves until the middle of the month.)
I won't tell you that I always like the lead time of a monthly magazine. But we do some things that competitors sometimes don't. First, we concentrate our most time-sensitive material in the "Need to Know" section, which, because of the technology involved, closes just days before the magazine is printed. Second, we mail the magazine immediately, rather than timing the postal date to coincide with the newsstand date. Third and most important: We recommend stocks that make sense as long-term investments.<p>Let's look for a moment at <a name="NASD:ISIP"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14081"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Isis Pharmaceuticals</b></a>, the company we told you may become the next Microsoft. When we put the magazine together, Isis was trading at about $11 a share. On May 2, by which time subscribers should have received the magazine, it was at $13.75. On May 14, when the magazine reached newsstands, it was up to $18.63. As I write this, on July 22, Isis is trading at $16.62. I understand that it's painful to miss a price move. Nevertheless, this kind of short-term fluctuation isn't very important in terms of the kind of investing this magazine endorses.<p>As always, you can write to me at 575 Lexington Avenue, New York, NY 10022, or send me a fax at 212-980-4307. My E-mail
address: john_koten@worth.com.<p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/2pages.gif"><br>About 2 pages

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

<font size=+1><b>Company Index</b><br>
</font>						<a href="#NASD:MSFT">Microsoft Corporation</a><br>

						<a href="#NASD:ISIP">Isis Pharmaceuticals, Inc.</a><br>

