<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/09-Forward Thinking</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/09-Forward Thinking</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
Our intention is to provide readers with a concise snapshot of the current financial climate--one not available anywhere else<p>By W. Randall Jones<p>Since we launched it a year ago, Need to Know has become one of the most popular features in Worth. Earlier this year, supportive comments from readers prompted us to expand the section to four pages, adding more information about mutual funds and a map that tracks the performance of global markets. Those additions were introduced in our May issue.<p>This month we've expanded Need to Know again, and in a big way. We've added five more pages and a dozen new charts and graphs. Three pages now focus on stocks, two on mutual funds, and one on bonds and other fixed-income instruments.<p>Our intention is to provide our readers with a concise yet relatively complete snapshot of the current financial climate--an intelligent summary not available anywhere else. While designing the expanded section, we sought out some of the best financial minds and collectors of data around. We're particularly pleased with our source for information about the flow of money into mutual funds. AMG Data Services, a supplier of financial data based in Arcata, California, found a way to help us get our readers the most up-to-date information available in a monthly financial publication. Have a look at Mutual Fund Laboratory on page 31.<p>That's just one example. Another is Jim Stack, the president of InvesTech Research, a market-research firm in Whitefish, Montana, who has helped us create a new market indicator that uses the performance of utility and brokerage stocks to forecast the direction of the market. You can find Stack's indicator, The Composite Bellwether, in Market Radar on page 26. Goldman Sachs, <a name="NYSE:MS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11018"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Morgan Stanley</b></a>, Standard & Poor's Compustat, CDA/Investnet, and Value Line also agreed to provide critical information for the new section.<p>Another change: We've thrown open Need to Know's Ten Stocks column to outside players. This month, on page 27, Louis Navellier, publisher of MPT Review, picks ten issues to consider, while David Tyce, who writes the newsletter Behind the Numbers, picks ten to avoid. <p>Timeliness is critical to us at Worth and is an especially important part of Need to Know. The section is the last component of the magazine we produce, and it's shipped to the printing plant on a different timetable from the rest of Worth's pages. We hope you'll like the result. I'd be interested to hear your thoughts about the expansion of Need to Know or about any other part of our magazine. Call me at 212-223-3100, send a fax to 212-223-1597, or write to me at 575 Lexington Avenue, New York, NY 10022.<p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
