	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/11-By  the Book</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>By  the Book</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/11-By  the Book</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						November 1994
Worth magazine/Options<p>BY THE BOOK
Daily planners let busy people schedule in style.<p>By Monica Corcoran<p>Forget about the Newton. Corporate dons and divas still prefer bulging daily planners over electronic organizers to take control of their lives and signify social stature. A casual flip through the pages in front of clients and colleagues reveals who you know, where you eat, and how often you are called upon to RSVP.<p>More than 10 million Americans rely on these compact calendars to plot their every move. Cindy Crawford manages her own schedule with an organizer, and some ultra-harried types have it even better -- Donna Karan's assistant carries her planner for her. Jerome Want, managing director of Organization Strategies in New York, prefers a paper planner to an electronic one: "It makes a better record when filing taxes, and it won't ever break down."<p>Consultants aren't alone in touting the day planner. Taste makers from Giorgio Armani to architect Michael Graves know that the book you carry reveals as much about you as what's written on the pages. They both offer sleek leather books that marry fashion with function. Timberland is joining them with a line of desktop agendas designed for their customers' rugged tastes. But the most prestigious of planners can't be bought. The embossed, cobalt blue, bound leather book of Paris's Hotel Ritz is bestowed upon its VIP guests. According to spokeswoman Celine Canot, the hotel fields about ten requests per week for the planner during the first months of the year. "Of course," she says, "we are highly selective about who we send one to." Bien sur. <p><p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
