	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Extra Terrestrials</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/10-Extra Terrestrials</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						October 1994
Worth magazine/Options<p>EXTRA TERRESTRIALS
There's a whole world of globes out there.<p>By Dean Robinson<p>Globes are spinning everywhere. decorators and interior designers, installing cachet more than accuracy, are snapping up antique globes for their worldly clients; new globes are exerting their own pull. Bryan Hollingsworth of globe maker George F. Cram attributes the rise in new globe sales to stabler world borders in the last couple of years, an increased emphasis on geographical literacy, and companies' growing tendency to look abroad. "They need to know where their customers and suppliers are," he says.<p>Such global awareness helps explain the decorative success of New York City's Mappamondo restaurant, which is crowded with globes. "People love it," says manager Jessica Seal. "They get a globe and put it on a table and talk about where they've been."<p>Antique globe dealers talk about where they're going. George Glazer, who specializes in 19th-century globes and prints, says globes remain a bargain compared to fine art. But the appearance of even a few more collectors -- such as fashion mogul Gianni Versace, who displays dozens of old globes in his Milan house -- may push the antique globe market into a new orbit. <p>Already, according to Robert Israel of Kentshire Galleries, a pair of globes that sold for $10,000 six years ago can go for five times that amount today. Still, Israel advises people not to invest, but to buy for enjoyment. "Of course," he says, "likely as not, globes will be a good investment." <p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Investing Strategies

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
