	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/09-The Personal Golf Pro</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>The Personal Golf Pro</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/09-The Personal Golf Pro</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						September 1994
Worth magazine/Options<p>THE PERSONAL GOLF PRO<p>By David E. Outerbridge<p>I'm as passionate about my golf game as any other novice, and as easily frustrated. On a good day golf seems like the game I was born to play, but on a bad day my shots careen off center like drugged gulls in an errant wind. <p>It was after a bad day that I called the United States Senior Golf Academy (USSGA) in Melbourne, Florida, and signed up for some intensive study. The academy guarantees five days of instruction with a teaching ratio of three to one or less for $1,685. For a $295 premium, it offers one-on-one instruction -- the same ratio that pro Nick Faldo gets from his coach David Leadbetter.<p>I indulged in one-on-one lessons from Tim Peightal, a licensed class-A PGA professional who gave me eight hours a day of advice, monitoring, correction, drills, video analysis, and coached play. During my week at the school I found that one-on-one offered two important advantages for absorbing all this tutelage. First, there was complete flexibility within a day's schedule. I was never fettered by anyone else's need to stick with any one element of the game. For example, when I demonstrated an ability to get out of a bunker, we abandoned that part of the curriculum.<p>The second advantage to one-on-one instruction became clear during the afternoon playing lessons. As we drove to our next shot or waited for a group in front to clear the green, Peightal would ask, for example, what my "swing thought" had been on the prior shot. This allowed him to tailor his instruction and suggested a line of questioning from me.<p>There was also time for mini lectures. One afternoon Peightal talked about the average player's fixation with the driver and corresponding lack of regard for the putter. As a putter is used more than twice as much as the driver, Peightal spoke of the importance of the putter's being well-suited to the player. Mine, he said, was not, and he explained why. Then, after our round, he redesigned my putter, cutting two inches off the shaft, adding an oversize grip, and placing strips of lead tape on the blade. I putted better thereafter.<p>On the last day, as Peightal added one final piece of instruction and an accompanying drill, all the changes and partial improvements of the week suddenly came together. I now understand the golf swing. I understand its physics, its feel, its dynamics, its parts, its whole. When I make a bad shot I can self-correct. My practice has become productive -- I'm not just smacking balls and hoping for a good shot. I am analyzing, refining, and grooving proper techniques.<p>Is this kind of result worth five days of hard work? Ask any golfer you know. <p>WHAT YOU GET:
-> Over 42 hours of personal golf instruction.
-> One video of you on the course with advice narrated by your instructor.
-> Seven days of lodging and most meals.<p>EXTRAS:
-> None. It would be overload.<p>WHAT YOU MIGHT BUY INSTEAD:
-> Seven Big Bertha War Bird clubs with graphite shafts.
-> One and three-quarter days of a two-day retreat with David Leadbetter. 
-> Eight rounds of golf at Pebble Beach.<p>BOTTOM LINE:
-> The United States Senior Golf Academy is for all ages and skill levels. The students during my week all stated that their games were much improved. The one-on-one feature is a bargain, but requires a commitment to very hard work. For information, call 800-654-5752.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Travel Industry, Sports Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

