	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Fitness in the Bag</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/09-Fitness in the Bag</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						September 1994
Worth magazine/Options<p>FITNESS IN THE BAG<p>By Lauren Goldstein<p>What's easier to pack than a personal trainer and works muscles just as hard? The Lifeline Portable Gym, a low-tech (and low price--about $60) exercise kit bought for road workouts by actors Paul Newman and Leslie Nielsen and the man who guards Madonna's fat-free body. The two-pound Lifeline Portable Gym, which consists of a lifting bar, treadmill belt, and elastic cable, is just one of many portable resistance-training regimens available now. Resistance equipment such as Dyna-Bands (three-foot strips of latex) and hand paddles for use while swimming can yield the "same results for aerobics and toning that you would get at the gym," says Amie Hoff, a personal trainer at Equinox Fitness Club in New York City. <p>For a cardiovascular workout while traveling, Gray Cook, a physical therapist with the Stewart Physical Therapy Group in Salisbury, North Carolina, suggests the old-fashioned method of jumping rope, or hooking the Lifeline up as a treadmill. By wearing the Lifeline's belt and running against the resistance of the rubber tubing, joggers can create the effect of heading uphill. Most Olympic ski teams use this resistance to simulate skiing by jumping from side to side.
Exercise helps to alleviate the stresses and strains of travel. "The most important thing," says Cook, "is to be consistent. And to eliminate as many excuses as possible." Because without the services of your personal trainer, the only person to push you on the road is you. <p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

