	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/04-The Tao of Tea</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/04-The Tao of Tea</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>By Tish Durkin<p>Creative caffeine alert: there's a brand-new beverage buzz. It's tea. Yes, despite its 5,000 years of age and well-known function as the nectar of English nannies, the "cup of humanity" has remade its image for the nineties. It's postmodern. "I have pipes on the ceilings and linens on the table," boasts Miriam Novalle of the sleek new T, a tea salon in the basement of the Guggenheim Museum SoHo in New York City. (She also has 650 eccentric teapots and her own fragranced black teas, from Whispering Heaven to Zen Blend and back). It's posh. "There's a new snob appeal about Darjeeling," says Jason Goodwin, author of the historical tome A Time for Tea--and no wonder; the best "single garden" varietal can go for $200 a pound. It's Parisian--or Muscovite or Delhian, as you please. Lisa's Tea Treasures, franchising nationwide as we sip, serves total teas from all of the above. It's potent. Disciples will swear on a stack of unfermented leaves that green tea fights cancer--but properly served, any tea should combat the strains of life.<p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
