<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/03-Brief Encounter</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/03-Brief Encounter</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>By Gail Glickman Horwood<p>The organization man is a vanishing breed, and so is his briefcase. The hard slim case he once carried paperwork in has been replaced by a softer, more stylish silhouette. "It's been an evolution," says Jill Golden of Coach leather goods. "As women rose through the ranks, personal style became more of a professional issue."<p>The newest shapes play off retro looks but appeal to both men and women. Color has become more expressive: Louis Vuitton's Taiga line is available only in forest green. And browns are challenging black as the new neutral. The briefcases also offer the kind of flexibility today's executive needs. There are compartments that accommodate computers, cellular phones, and faxes, and detachable straps are a common option. Bree's sporty briefcases can even convert to a backpack. With her briefcase on her back, Organization Woman has her hands free to adapt to the evolving workplace.<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
