	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/03-The Age of India</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/03-The Age of India</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>Victoria conquered it. Kipling covered it. Richard Attenborough made it a star. India has been on our western minds for a long, long time. This spring, though, it will be in our faces. Or rather, on our movie screens, with In Custody, Merchant Ivory Productions' gripping drama about--yes--Urdu... in our bookstores, with Bombay-born Ismail Merchant's pungent cookbook, Passionate Meals: The New Indian Cuisine for Fearless Cooks and Adventurous Eaters (Hyperion, $27.50)... on our pulse points, with Casmir, the rare scent that can count mango and coconut among its top notes--and the Taj Mahal as the model for its bottle--out this month from Lancaster... and quite literally over our heads, at New York's Metropolitan Museum of Art's brand-new Irving Galleries for South and Southeast Asian Art, where, precious Buddhas and Bodhisattvas aside, the biggest eyeful may be had by looking up at the carved teakwood dome that has come all the way from 16th-century Gujarat.<p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
