<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/02-Roses in Winter</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-Roses in Winter</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>By Tish Durkin<p>Gertrude stein isn't alone in thinking a "rose is a rose is a rose," but the best cupids know better. Here's how to make a lasting impression.<p>Surrender the red. Long-stemmed reds don't exactly scream originality. At least contemplate the growing bounty of colors and names at your disposal: the tall, creamy, slow-opening oceana, a fabulously fragrant orange morella, the feisty South American lambada. <p>Handle with care. "If the head of the rose is firm, then it's a sign that the rose is fresh," says Gary Buckwald of Surroundings in Manhattan. Good roses should last five days. <p>Send a setting. Unless your beloved is a closet florist or a ballerina taking a bow, forgo the long-stemmed bouquet for a vase-and-all arrangement ready to be plunked down.<p>Surprise your valentine, not your florist. The cost of roses routinely rises by at least 25 percent around Valentine's Day (from the usual $75 for a dozen high-quality blooms). Order at least a week in advance.<p>Invest in the best. The Rolls of roses is the pale apricot, long-stemmed, long-blooming Beaute. It'll cost you the moon, but that's a pittance to pay for love.      <p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td width=390>
	
		<center>
		<p>
