	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 97/02-Outfront: Bill Shills: Will Kill!</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/02-Outfront: Bill Shills: Will Kill!</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Teri Karush Rogers<p>
"Collectors have every incentive to beat the crap out of you over the phone," says Benjamin Dover, author of the self-help book Life After Debt. "Probably 60 percent of their tactics are illegal." Take, for instance, the creep who threatened Marianne Driscol of Texas. Not only did he claim to have planted a bomb in Driscol's office, but he also said a hit man had been hired -- all this over a $2,000 Visa bill. Driscol later won an $11 million judgment against Household Credit Services, which has appealed the ruling. Meanwhile, pit-bull collection practices run rampant. Impersonating an insurance agent with a claim check to get a return call, tacking on additional fees, and falsely implying that an arrest or property seizure is impending are common and illegal tactics. And don't expect to get revenge easily. Dover says that few attorneys will take harassment cases, which take years to resolve.
KEYWORDS:
collection, debt, dunning

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
