	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 97/01-Hey, I Didn't Have a Triple Bypass</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/01-Hey, I Didn't Have a Triple Bypass</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Monica Corcoran<p>
Ambulance chasers, the joke goes, file suits before the blood dries. Medical Recovery Service waits until the ink sets. The Illinois-based company peruses hospital bills for overages, disputes the charges, and splits what's recovered with convalescing clients. There's no shortage of pain. According to a study by research firm Equifax, more than 90 percent of all hospital bills are flawed. The most common overcharges? Lab tests, X rays, and even surgical procedures that were never performed. The supply costs hurt, too -- such as the $11.50 box of tissues (billed as a mucus-removal system) and a $17 "mouthwash" kit made up of only a toothbrush, paste, and floss.
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
