				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/11-Hey Chief, This Vote's for You</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Eat, drink, and be patriotic.<p>
By Melissa Jeffries<p>
All those political debates and empty campaign promises can be tough to digest. But thanks to New Amsterdam beer, we the people can wash that rhetoric down with Election '96 Campaign Ale. <p>
"We'd like this to be known as 'Ale to the Chief,'" says a spokesman from the beer company. Let it be noted, by the way, that New Amsterdam exhorts voters to sober up before they pull the lever: don't drink and vote, warn Campaign Ale posters and buttons. <p>
No need to worry about imbibing on an empty stomach either -- pick up a box of Kraft's presidential edition of macaroni and cheese, available in elephant- or donkey-shaped pasta. The patriotic grub debuted at the summer conventions. Now, how about some First Lady Alka-Seltzer?<p>
KEYWORDS:
marketing, gimick, politics, election, food, alcohol, beverage

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
