<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/10-Trend Spotter</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/10-Trend Spotter</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Melissa Jeffries<p>
HOT WHEELS. Looks like Easy Riders are now easy targets. The National Insurance Crime Bureau reports that the number of motorcycles stolen annually has jumped 46 percent since 1992. <p>
SKY SPA. Flying first-class has reached new heights. Virgin Atlantic Airways now offers manicures and massages on domestic flights, while both British Airways and Air France feature private cabins in first-class sections.<p>
POLITICALLY INCORRECT. Don't expect a feminine touch in the upcoming presidential duel. A recent poll of about 1,000 political TV ads, by professor June Speakman at Roger Williams University, found that only 5 percent used a female voice. "As one consultant told me, the voice of God is a male voice," says Speakman. And the voice of reason?<p>
WORK RELIEF. Corporate mergers have become less risky for employees. A study by outplacement firm Challenger, Gray & Christmas reveals that mergers are up 23 percent since last year but that layoffs following these unions have dropped 31 percent.<p>
GOING FOR BROKE. The American Bankers Association reports that personal bankruptcies are up 21 percent since last year. <p>
TAKEN FOR A RIDE. According to the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, the number of odometer-fraud complaints by the purchasers of used cars has soared from 45 per month to 24 per week.	 <p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
