					<font size=4>
						April 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Outfront  <p> GOONS ON-LINE  <p> By Ted C. Fishman  <p> Arnold is a debt collector. He's big, chews a stogie, and looks like he packs a heater under his dark double-breasted suit. Luckily, Arnold won't pay you a visit any evening soon, no matter how much vig you owe the loan sharks. That's because he's a cartoon figure on the No Excuses!! Web site,  to our knowledge the first debt-collection service to appear on the Internet's World Wide Web(http://www.arnoldbeckerstevens.com/stannet/abs/welcome.html. Arnold is the mascot of Arnold, Becker & Stevens, a New York City collection agency, whose site includes a list of the firm's favorite excuses--which range from the classic ("My dog ate it") to the improbable ("I've been deceased for the last 18 months")--and all the forms clients need to expedite collection.<p>
KEYWORDS: Technology Industry

					</font>
