		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>April Fool's</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/04-April Fool's</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						April 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Outfront  <p> APRIL FOOL'S  <p> April is the cruelest month--at least for poets and tax cheats. Here, in honor of all the honestlers, are a few of the stellar scofflaws, along with their penalties: Willie Nelson, $5.4 million...Burt Reynolds, $138.64...Darryl Strawberry, $350,000...Leona Helmsley,$9 million...Aldo Gucci, $30,000...Rev. Sun Myung Moon, $25,000...Andrew Mellon, $485,809...Ronald Reagan, $4,663...Alphonse Capone, $80,000...Charlie Hustle (a.k.a.Pete Rose), $50,000...Bud Abbott, $500,000...Spiro Agnew, $10,000...Sophia Loren, $14,500. <p>
KEYWORDS: Taxation, Entertainment Industry
