	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>How to Snag a Free Honeymoon</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/06-How to Snag a Free Honeymoon</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						June 1995 <p>Worth magazine/Outfront  <p> HOW TO SNAG A FREE HONEYMOON  <p> By Monica Corcoran  <p> Dianne Martinez and Bill Hale weren't sure how to handle gifts when planning their upcoming wedding. Martinez, 47, a second-time bride, had no interest in china or flatware. "We already have all that household stuff," she says. "But we would never ask for money." Not explicitly, anyway. Instead, they registered with a travel agency for a six-day bicycle trip through France's Burgundy Valley. Estimated cost: $4,000.  <p> That concept the honeymoon registry is fast becoming the talk of the bridal industry. "In nearly 50 percent of weddings these days, it's a remarriage for the bride or groom," says Alan Fields, coauthor of Bridal Bargains. "They don't need that fifth toaster."Worldtek Travel agrees; the agency recently launched an official honeymoon registry package.  <p> But not everyone is in favor of bucking tradition. "I talked a bride out of it because I think it's tacky," says Roberta Fleming, owner of Lace and Promises, a bridal consultancy in Baltimore."It's like saying, Hey folks, help us pay for our wedding.'"  <p> Hey, why not? Etiquette didn't deter Shalley Parmenter and Tom Joyner of Flagstaff, Arizona, from registering their honeymoon. Last October, the newlyweds spent three weeks backpacking through Chile; wedding guests chipped in some $3,000 toward the excursion."Some people thought it was rude," says Joyner. "But they could buy us crystal instead."   <p> <p>
KEYWORDS: Travel Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

