						May 1995
Worth magazine/Outfront<p>GLOBAL CHIC
A checklist of cool in Winterset, Iowa, the seat of Madison County:<p>"Scooping the loop" on Friday night, when the teen center is closed--that is, driving slowly up and down John Wayne Boulevard, turning around at the car wash on the south end and the Hardee's at the north<p>Line dancing on Saturday night at the Gold Rush bowling alley<p>Eating a "Francesca's Regret" at the Montross Pharmacy: An apple dumpling covered with caramel and frozen yogurt, topped with a cherry<p>Sitting on the third stool at the Northside Cafe, where Clint Eastwood, as Robert Kincaid, ate a ham-and-cheese sandwich during filming of The Bridges of Madison County<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Entertainment Industry

