<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 95/02-Tip and Run</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Tip and Run</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/02-Tip and Run</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						February 1995
Worth magazine/Outfront<p>TIP AND RUN<p>If you think you're not getting your money's worth out of tips, maybe you're not sending the right message. Members of a group called Tippers Anonymous have solved that problem: When they leave a gratuity, the statement comes through loud and clear. The group's trademark is its calling card--a waiter's report card that members leave with (or without) their tip. Diners fill out the report card to rate their service from excellent to poor and then tip accordingly. That doesn't mean cheaply, though. TA founder Robert Farrington isn't opposed to generous tipping; in fact, he recalls recently leaving a 20 percent gratuity. Instead, the report cards are dedicated to restoring the idea that a tip is a reward, not a right. Best of all, diners need not worry about violent retaliation by an undertipped waiter. "The beauty of the report cards," Farrington says with a chuckle, "is that they let you make your point and get out of there." <p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

