<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 95/02-Me? I'm a 1040EZ</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>95/02-Me? I'm a 1040EZ</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						There's not likely to be much heavy breathing on New York City's latest 900 number. But moans may be heard, as folks discuss their tax dilemmas on this new CPA chat line. At $3.99 a minute, the service promises to "make taxes less taxing" by demystifying everything from estate issues to corporate refunds. But prepare before you call, because the meter will be running, advises Alan Reed, the CPA behind it all. "You have to know how to ask the right questions," he says. At Reed's suggestion, we anonymously hit him with a few tricky tax queries about home offices and real estate. "His advice was right on," says a fellow CPA whom we asked to vet the answers. But H&R Block needn't close up shop. This hotline could be costly for a filer with, say, overseas mutual funds. "It's in the same class as Dial-a-Doc," says Rick Telberg, editor at Accounting Today. "But what will kill you in taxes is what you don't know."<p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Taxation
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
