	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/09-100 Grand</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/09-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						The challenge: Blow a tax-free windfall of $100,000 -- imaginary, we're afraid -- on five items. This month's players are three top chefs. Jacques Pepin writes a column for the New York Times and this fall will host a third season of Today's Gourmet on public TV. Pastry chef Nancy Silverton is a co-owner of La Brea Bakery and Campanile, a trendy Los Angeles dining spot. Stephan Pyles recently opened the superhot Star Canyon restaurant in Dallas, home of "New Texas cuisine."<p>
JACQUES PEPIN<p>-> $30,000 to help pay the mortgage for the James Beard Foundation, a showcase for good food.<p>-> $15,000 to sharpen all the knives in all the kitchens he'll visit during the next year.<p>-> $15,000 to give lessons to young chefs so they'll serve food warm, properly seasoned, "and not arranged like a Japanese garden."<p>-> $20,000 to fund an apartment in Brussels for his daughter Claudine, a political science student.<p>-> $20,000 to throw a champagne-and-caviar party for himself and his friends.<p><p>NANCY SILVERTON<p>-> $20,000 to landscape her backyard a la Martha Stewart, with a wood-burning oven and barbecue -- "a little bit of Connecticut in L.A."<p>-> $20,000 for giving to close friends and saying, "Buy whatever you want."<p>-> $20,000 to squirrel away for her three kids, to help them go to college or travel in Europe.<p>-> $20,000 to donate to the Pediatric AIDS Foundation.<p>-> $20,000 to indulge a longtime fantasy: Handing out $100 bills at Florence and Normandie, the corner in South Central L.A. where the riots began.<p><p>STEPHAN PYLES<p>-> $20,000 to take his kitchen staff to Oaxaca, Mexico, to experience firsthand the inspiration for his restaurant's food.<p>-> $20,000 to cover the restaurant's losses from such a trip -- "otherwise my partners wouldn't let me do it."<p>-> $10,000 to install gas lines and a commercial stove in his home.<p>-> $40,000 to throw a party on a ranch in his native West Texas. "There'd be spit-roasted goat, barbecued everything, and the Gipsy Kings would play."<p>-> $10,000 to help Share Our Strength feed undernourished children.<p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/2pages.gif"><br>About 2 pages

					</font>
					</tt>
