	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/08-Sinking Feeling</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
Trying to build a floating utopia isn't exactly a profitable venture.<p>By Jim Melloan<p>WHO HE IS: Eric Klien, 28-year-old computer programmer and founder of the Atlantis Project.<p>WHAT HE WANTS TO DO: Build utopia.<p>WHERE HE WANTS TO PUT IT: On a network of hexagonal floating platforms off the coast of Panama.<p>HOW HE'S DOING: Not well. The Atlantis Project just shut down; Klien will spend "the foreseeable future" paying off its debts.<p>SO HE'S GIVEN UP? No, another try may be in the offing.<p>HOW KLIEN ENVISIONS UTOPIA: As a libertarian paradise with minimal government. It would be called Oceania.<p>WHY "THE ATLANTIS PROJECT," THEN? Atlantis is the lost continent buy also alludes to Atlas Shrugged by Klien hero Ayn Rand.<p>WHAT WOULD BE PERMITTED IN OCEANIA: Drugs, prostitution.<p>WHAT WOULD BE ILLEGAL: Taxes.<p>ESTIMATED COST TO BUILD THE FIRST NINETY 1.6-ACRE HEXAGONS: At least $1 billion.<p>HOW MUCH KLIEN HAD RAISED FROM INVESTORS: About $50,000, plus $100,000 in donations.<p>THE BRAIN BEHIND OCEANIA'S DESIGN: Architect Sten Sjostrand, who also designed a floating hotel for divers exploring Australia's Great Barrier Reef.<p>WHY THAT IDEA WAS A FLOP: Wherever the hotel was put, it killed the reef.<p>WHAT HAPPENED TO THE HOTEL: Japanese investors had it towed to Vietnam, where it has done better.<p>HOW KLIEN MET SJOSTRAND: Through Mike Oliver, a concentration-camp survivor who tried -- and failed -- to build utopia on an uninhabited Pacific island.<p>WHAT KLIEN IS DOING NOW: Looking for computer-programming work. He's also "glad to take donations."<p>SO, NO MAN-MADE ISLANDS FOR A WHILE? Actually, Universal Studios is building one off Hawaii for the filming of Waterworld, a special-effects blockbuster that will star Kevin Costner.<p>PROGRESS OF THAT PROJECT: Construction is underway. The movie will be released next summer.<p>THE MORAL: Write a script, not a constitution.

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
