				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/08-Money Spy</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
The Debts of Zsa Zsa Gabor<p>"Sorry, dahling, I'm broke." That was the essence of Zsa Zsa Gabor's retort to Elke Sommer, the aging German bombshell to whom Gabor was ordered to pay a $1.25 million slander judgment. The feuding celebrities couldn't even agree on that much, however: Sommer recently filed a motion to dismiss Gabor's March petition for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection. "Gabor could pay up if she sold some of her property," says David Reeder, Sommer's lawyer. "Chapter 11 is for people with true financial difficulty -- and she's not one of them."<p>Far be it from us to judge the merits of either side in this catfight. But the documents filed in the case by Gabor, 76, provide an interesting look into the financial life of someone who's known mostly for being rich and famous.<p>A sampling of her debts:<p>-> To Melvin Belli, the well-known attorney: $150,000<p>-> To Courtesy Stables, for purchase of horses: $26,812.50<p>-> To American Fence: $6,088.82<p>-> To Citibank Visa: $9,662.58<p>-> To Dynamic Private Duty Nursing: $507.15<p>-> To Beverly Hills Small Animal Hospital: $785.25<p>-> To Hollywood Fantasy: $140,000 (a television production company)<p>-> To Bloomingdale's: $2,800<p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
