	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/08-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						July/August 1994
Worth magazine/Outfront<p>100 GRAND <p>The challenge: Blow a tax-free windfall of $100,000 -- imaginary, we're afraid -- on five items. Our players this time hope to become America's latest heroes by helping the U.S. soccer team do well in the World Cup in July. The key to success may lie with goalie and team captain Tony Meola, whose skill will be tested by Swiss and Colombian attackers. Sweeper Marcelo Balboa is a seasoned veteran who played in the last World Cup. At 23, defender Alexi Lalas is a new star who's great in the air: He scored six goals with his head last year.<p>
TONY MEOLA<p>-> $30,000 to swap acting tips over an Italian dinner with Al Pacino, Robert De Niro, Joe Pesci, Andy Garcia, Danny Aiello, and Danny De Vito.<p>-> $10,000 to buy tickets for underprivileged kids to see the U.S. team's games.<p>-> $20,000 to rescue as many stray and unwanted dogs as possible.<p>-> $10,000 for a trip to Hawaii after the World Cup is over, "including a $1,000 tip to the operator to keep my phone from ringing."<p>-> $30,000 to invest in a one-year-old thoroughbred racehorse for him and wife Colleen.<p><p>MARCELO BALBOA <p>-> $15,000 for a new <a name="NYSE:HDI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10706"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Harley Davidson</b></a>. "Any kind, as long as Rebecca De Mornay can fit on the back."<p>-> $15,000 to take Helen Hunt to Monaco for the weekend on a private plane.<p>-> $20,000 to start a catalog called 'Celo's Secret. "I'm not the model, though -- I'll leave that to Rebecca and Helen."<p>-> $40,000 for a black BMW 325i convertible, fully loaded.<p>-> $10,000 as a gift to the Magic Johnson Foundation, which supports AIDS research. "That's my goody-goody item."<p><p>ALEXI LALAS<p>-> $5,000 for a Slurpee machine. Both nozzles would serve cherry, his favorite flavor.<p>-> $20,000 for music gear, including a couple of vintage Gibson guitars and an old Stratocaster.<p>-> $50,000 to buy some real estate on the Upper Peninsula in his native Michigan.<p>-> $5,000 for four season tickets to the Detroit Red Wings.<p>-> $20,000 for a huge party after the World Cup. "Everyone would be invited -- even our opponents. It'd be a down-and-dirty, kegs and T-shirts affair."<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
