<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/05-Get Your Kicks</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/05-Get Your Kicks</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
As World Cup tickets soar in value, here's an insider's guide to the resale market<p>By James Buckley Jr.<p>If you own any of the 3.6 million tickets for this summer's soccer World Cup, count yourself lucky: You're on the right side of a big seller's market. Already, some single tickets are going for twice the price of the four- or five-game packages offered for $105 to $400 last year.<p>Prescient buyers snapped up those packages without knowing what teams they'd see. Once teams were announced in December, most tickets got more valuable--and some became the equivalent of gold dust. By now, the chance of paying face value for a ticket is as slim as the U.S. team's prospect of making the World Cup final.<p>As a result, the resale market is taking off, despite extra-tough conditions imposed by the tournament's organizers. The worst snag--apart from the possible illegality of some resales--is that no actual tickets have been issued yet: To stymie counterfeiting, ticket buyers have only gotten a confirmation letter so far. The real tickets won't be distributed until this month. That has made reselling a matter of faith and contracts, rather than a simple hand-it-over transaction.<p>For most World Cup ticket holders, the easiest and best thing to do is to attend the game and be thankful. But if that ticket really was an investment, and resale is legal in your area, here's how to cash in. Ticket buyers, of course, can turn these tips around.<p>-> sell or hold? If you've got tickets to a less-popular game--Saudi Arabia vs. Morocco, say, or Cameroon vs.Sweden--get what you can right now. For the top first-round matchups, as well as later games, hang tight: Foreign fans will be waving huge wads of bills near game day.<p>-> The ethnic card. U.S. demand will be highest in immigrant enclaves, so advertising in the right ethnic newspapers can pay off. Another trick is to call popular ethnic restaurants and bars. Don't laugh; they may be the busiest ticket-trading centers of all.<p>-> Get on-line. The sports areas on computer-chat networks such as America Online and CompuServe are active trading forums.<p>-> Go global. More foreigners than Americans will be looking for tickets. Try using a friend in a relevant city--Berlin for Germany games, for example--as a go-between. Some sellers are even placing ads in foreign papers.<p>-> See your agent. Dozens of official World Cup travel agencies around the globe are selling tournament packages. Some may not have enough tickets to offer as many tours as they'd like. Call and make a deal.<p>-> Good as gold. Finally, if you're in the enviable position of owning a ticket for the July 17 final at the Rose Bowl--go. Reselling may get you a 1,000 percent return, but you shouldn't miss one of the greatest spectacles in sport.<p>Even better, you could just give it to me.<p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Sports Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
