	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/04-Opportunity Knocks</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/04-Opportunity Knocks</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						
Looking for a hot franchise idea? Try selling lube jobs door-to-door. (Really.)<p>By Dean Robinson<p>Franchising is bigger than ever: Entrepreneur magazine's annual Franchise 500 issue actually lists 873 franchisors. Investors and potential franchisees can be forgiven, then, for failing to spot the recent rotisserie-chicken craze in a crowded field. So you won't miss another <a name="NASD:BOST"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16244"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Boston Chicken</b></a>, we asked some experts to predict the next big franchise opportunity.   <p>expert:  Edward Kushell, president of Franchise Consulting Group, based in Los Angeles.
next big franchise: Fresh bagels--but better-tasting ones than current offerings.
why: Healthy food, good return on investment, chance to save the world from supermarket bagels.
current players: No national player meets Kushell's standard. But top chains include Manhattan Bagel, Chesapeake Bagel Bakery, Skolniks Bagel Bakery.<p>expert:  Regina Gardner, board member of the International Franchise Association and owner of a travel franchise in Houston.
next big franchise: Business services, such as postal centers, temp-worker providers, and travel agencies.
why: "The 1990s are the era of service," as she keeps hearing.
current players: Voice-Tel Enterprises, Interim Services, Mail Boxes Etc.<p>expert:  Gladys Glickman, author of Franchising.
next big franchise: Fast food in Eastern Europe.
why: In developing countries, it's a cheap, popular, and easy-to-start business.
current players: <a name="NYSE:MCD"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10974"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>McDonald's</b></a>, Little Caesars Pizza, Arby's, Burger King.<p>expert:  Pete Harman, first and largest independent franchisee of KFC--in 1952 he agreed to pay Colonel Sanders a nickel for every chicken he sold.
next big franchise: Buffet-style dining.
why: People want healthier food and greater variety at a good price.
current players: Sizzler International, Golden Corral. Stacy Buffet may start franchising.<p>expert:  Susan Kezios, president and founder of Women in Franchising and the American Franchisee Association.
next big franchise: Home-based service franchises, such as mobile dry cleaning and mobile auto detailing.
why: For those with $20,000 or less to invest, this is a promising franchise area--and customers like vendors who come to their homes.
current players: Pressed4Time, International Flying Colors, Oil Butler International.<p>expert:  Robert Purvin, chairman of the American Association of Franchisees and Dealers.
next big franchise: The information superhighway.
why: "It has a lot of sex appeal."
Current players: None, but he envisions local, brand-name on-line communities: "Someone will figure out how to sell a franchise." <p><p>
KEYWORDS: Small Business Ownership

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
