					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>A checklist of cool for status seekers in Hong Kong<p>--Hiring a Gurkha bodyguard, known for their endurance and loyalty
--Having a valet screen your pocket-phone calls
--Hiring a spy to check up on your kids while they're studying abroad
--Having a foreign passport, ensuring safety if things get hairy in 1997
--Investing in parking spaces, which go for six figures
--For aspiring young Chinese executives, taking a cool English name--such as Money or Sweet and Sour
--Buying a great license plate at auction--anything with an 8 is considered lucky<p>

