<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/04-Beating the Odds</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/04-Beating the Odds</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>Tired of being a lottery loser? Stop being a snob and try sweepstakes instead. Many cost only a 29-cent stamp and offer far shorter odds than Lotto. For those too harried to affix every "Early Bird" sticker, some tips: Avoid Ed McMahon and other huge mail shots--the odds are as bad as you think. Focus on obscure contests with opaque rules and lots of runner-up prizes. In general, the harder to enter, the easier to win. The current favorite of Jeffrey Sklar, co-publisher of Winning Sweepstakes Newsletter, is Hershey's "Apple-a-Day II" promotion, a computer giveaway.<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
