	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/04-100 Grand</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/04-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>The challenge: Blow a tax-free windfall of $100,000--imaginary, we're afraid--on five items. Our players this month are three daytime talk show hosts: Leeza Gibbons, veteran infotainer turned host of the NBC show that bears her name (but, alas, not John Tesh's anymore); former Cincinnati mayor Jerry Springer, who shuns frivolous prattle for more serious chat about what ails America; and newcomer Bertice Berry, a reformed stand-up comic and professor of sociology who hosts the syndicated show named for her.<p>LEEZA GIBBONS
--$50,000 to bribe Jackie Onassis onto her show.
--$20,000 for shrink sessions for some of her guests. "I mean, one is actually engaged to Richard Ramirez," the serial killer.
--$15,000 for a wet bar and Jacuzzi for the Leeza staff. "They work long, hard hours and deserve it."
--$10,000 to bribe the publisher of the Star, "so they'll stop putting me on the 'Would You Be Caught Dead in This Outfit?' page."
--$5,000 to pay fellow talker Jane Whitney to wear shoes on camera. "This really bugs me."<p>JERRY SPRINGER
--$49,960 for lunch with Claudia Schiffer--in Paris, bien sur. He supplies a scarily detailed breakdown, including airfare and hotel rooms (two) should lunch run late. 
--$11,000 to see every New York Yankees home game in style.
--$27,000 to buy and maintain a horse for his daughter Katie. 
--$5,570 to pay tuition at chauffeur school, get a license, and lease a limo "so I can drive Barbra Streisand around L.A. for three weeks." 
--$6,470 to buy lottery tickets for his audience and staff.<p>BERTICE BERRY
--$50,000 to fund a weekend dance hall for teenagers in Wilmington, Delaware, her hometown.
--$5,000 to thank Charles Barkley for being a role model, "even though he doesn't think he is one."
--$25,000 to establish an after-school vocational program, also in Wilmington. 
--$10,000 to help the homeless in Chicago, where she tapes her show.
--$10,000 to feed two nephews and a niece, of whom she recently gained custody. "Man, do those kids eat."<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
