	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/03-My First Time: Amy Domini</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>"In 1982 there was a huge write-up in the New York Times about monoclonal antibodies, a promising biotechnology technique. I was working as a broker in Boston and knew about Hybritech, a company using the method. It was risky--the stock would do really well or it would bomb.<p>"On November 5, I had my son Jotham. I decided that Hybritech would be a perfect birth gift for him, since he wouldn't need money for 18 years anyway. But it turned out to be a solid investment. I bought at $27.50 a share and sold in 1986, when <a name="NYSE:LLY"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10509"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Eli Lilly</b></a> bought the company--I was divesting stock in any company that did business with South Africa, which Lilly did. By then each share was worth $36, plus some delayed payments that were worth what I originally paid for Hybritech.<p>"Now my son is 11 and taking an active interest in his own account. His first selection, <a name="NYSE:MRV"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10665"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Marvel Entertainment</b></a>, is doing quite well."<p>Amy Domini, 44, is founder of the <a name="FUND:DSEFX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/DSEFX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Domini Social Equity Fund</b></a>. She has coauthored several books on ethical investing.<p><p>
KEYWORDS: Family Finance
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
