	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/03-100 Grand</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/03-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>The challenge: Blow a tax-free windfall of $100,000--imaginary, we're afraid--on five items. Our players this month are three columnists known for their devoted readership. Irv Kupcinet is hard-nosed author of the softhearted dish in "Kup's Column" in the Chicago Sun-Times. Now at W and WWD, Suzy, a.k.a. Aileen Mehle, has been wagging her pen for 30 years. Compared to these two, Clark DeLeon is a relative rookie, but he's already a favorite for his humorous column in the Philadelphia Inquirer.<p>IRV KUPCINET
$20,000 to fellow gossip Cindy Adams for her pipeline to Marla Maples and Donald Trump.
$30,000 to buy Phil Donahue's old dresses for Howard Stern, the radio shock jock.
$20,000 to pay for bratty actress Shannen Doherty (Beverly Hills 90210) to see a shrink.
$10,000 on behalf of President Clinton to pay for saxophone lessons for Russian proto-fascist Vladimir Zhirinovskiy.
$20,000 for baseball lessons for Michael Jordan.<p>SUZY
$50,000 to lease "an elegant but understated" Bentley, with a driver, for as long as possible.
$45,000 for a yearlong, around-the-world cruise on the QE2: "I need the rest."
$3,000 to add a closet to her townhouse apartment in New York. "But of course, there's no room for one."
$1,000 to her housekeeper Julia "for just being there and smiling, no matter what the weather."
$1,000 to her favorite charity, God's Love We Deliver.<p>CLARK DELEON
$50,000 to fund Just Cholesterol, an eatery serving only the four basic food groups--grease, starch, Italian salami, and beer.
$20,000 to open a cheese-steak stand on the Falklands. "You never know when they'll get sick of lamb chops."
$29,900 to develop a fragrance made with Oscar Mayer wieners. "Now everyone will be in love with you."
$57 to stockpile Heinz Ketchup. "I'm betting they'll make a 'New Coke' mistake."
$43 to develop a Rush Limbaugh Jazzercise video.<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/2pages.gif"><br>About 2 pages

