<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/02-My First Time</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-My First Time</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						"In 1983, I was sitting at home in Los Angeles watching television. A commercial for <a name="NASD:MCIC"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=13996"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>MCI</b></a> came on and said they would be providing telecommunications services for the 1984 Olympics. We had been following the Olympics at Financial News Network, and I remember thinking to myself, 'This can't lose.' I called a broker.<p>"We bought MCI at $40. Then I went on vacation. When I returned, there were messages from the broker asking me where the hell I had been. The stock had fallen out of bed--and I had bought at the absolute high. So what did I do? I bought more. The broker wanted me to cut my losses, but I didn't listen. It continued to drop. Come autumn of 1987, I finally threw in the towel and sold at $4 a share, near the lowest point MCI had ever hit.<p>"Now people ask me for recommendations, which I am loath to give. I just tell them to buy MCI."<p>Bill Griffeth, 37, is anchor of Money Wheel and host of Your Portfolio, both on CNBC.<p> <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

<font size=+1><b>Company Index</b><br>
</font>						<a href="#NASD:MCIC">MCI Communications Corporation</a><br>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td width=390>
	
