	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/02-Highway Robbery</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6007.html?worth+PCFN25.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN25.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-Highway Robbery</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						  
For taxpayers, it can cost plenty to live where the streets have no name collecting<p>By Dean Robinson<p>One thing stop signs don't stop is theft: They're the most frequently stolen traffic signs. But other signs are popular too. Washington, D.C., for example, has a problem with the all way signs below stop signs. Nevada loses a sign for Highway 50, "The Loneliest Road in America," about once a week. At $320 a pop, that adds up. New York City raises its most-stolen sign, wall st, 45 feet in the air to deter thieves. Alas, the $65 sign still gets stolen the day after it's replaced; now it's replaced only four times a year. Following are some other most-pilfered signs.<p>City: Los Angeles
Sign: Stoner Av
Why? Not just drugs--there are 17 Stoners gangs in L.A.
Cost to replace: $75<p>Cities: Detroit; St. Louis
Signs: Kaline Dr; James "Cool Papa" Bell Av.
Why? Al Kaline is a Hall of Famer;
Bell was the fastest Negro Leaguer.
Cost to replace: $41; $35<p>Cities: Milwaukee; Houston
Signs: Pabst Av; Corona
Why? Party on, dude.
Cost to replace: $80; $35<p>City: Nashville
Sign: Chet Atkins Blvd
Why? Light-fingered fans just love the fast-fingered guitar legend.
Cost to replace: $75<p>City: San Francisco
Signs: Haight, Ashbury
Why? If you can remember why, you don't deserve to keep them.
Cost to replace: $200<p>City: Seattle
Sign: nw 94 St
Why? Those wacky graduating seniors--it was 93 st last year.
Cost to replace: $75<p>Cities: Boston; San Diego
Signs: Beaver Pl; Climax Ct, Dick St
Why? Heh-heh, heh-heh. He said "climax."
Cost to replace: $25; $100
 <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
