				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-Global Chic</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 <p>
A checklist of cool for status seekers in New Orleans<p>--Shooting craps with Governor Edwards<p>--Paying someone to wait in line for you at Galatoire's on Friday afternoon, then having Imre as your waiter<p>--For whites, riding with the Zulu krewe during Mardi Gras; for blacks, riding with the Rex krewe<p>--Having ancestors buried in the cemetery walls<p>--Complaining about the Y'ats (declasse townies) at the Audubon Institute's Zoo-to-Do fund-raiser<p>--Having a pied-e-terre in the state-maintained part of the Pontalba, an apartment complex that dates to the 1850s<p> <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
