	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/02-Flesh Peddlers</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-Flesh Peddlers</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						  <p>Low on cash? Selling blood at $10 a pint, that old standby, is for wimps. For real money, try a kidney or a cornea. Macabre as it sounds, you can sell about 50 percent of your body, legally or illegally, without killing yourself--and those willing to shop around the globe can get close to $80,000 for their marketable parts. Kidneys are most in demand: The going rate is only $1,000 in China but rises to $30,000 in Poland. In India, probably the world's premier chop shop, two whole eyes go for $5,000; in Buenos Aires, it's $7,000 a cornea. Parting with a square inch of skin will earn you $20 in India, and anyone selling an arm or a leg there gets up to $4,000 for the tendons and skin. In Russia, where testicles are used for rejuvenating cream, a pair fetches $4,000. In the U.S., legal options include sperm at $44 a shot, undyed hair at $12 an ounce, and donating (not selling) eggs at up to $1,200--for your time, of course.
 <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
