				<font size=6><b>94/02-Changing Times</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 <p>Coin-operated machines meter our nation's misspent youth--and the measly haul from pinball machines is a reminder that no cultural totem is forever. These days, in fact, the only coin-operated entertainment that comes close to video games is acquiring lung cancer. <p>--Pinball machines: $2.26 million per year
--Kiddie rides: $3.6 million
--Gumball machines: $77 million
--Jukeboxes: $845 million
--Pool tables: $888 million
--Cigarette machines: $2.5 billion
--Video games: $2.72 billion
 <p><p>

					</font>
