				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/02-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 <p>The challenge: Blow a tax-free windfall of $100,000--imaginary, we're afraid--on five items. Our players this month are three comedians who are well qualified to spend our funny money: Janeane Garofalo, a regular on The Larry Sanders Show, who appears with her ex-television buddy Ben Stiller this month in Reality Bites, a movie comedy; Brooklyn-born Doug E. Doug, a star of the hit movie Cool Runnings; and Judy Tenuta, accordion-wielding high priestess of her own religion, Judyism.<p>JANEANE GAROFALO<p>--$40,000 in quarters, to be loaded into parking meters all over Los Angeles so nobody will get harassed for parking violations again.<p>--$20,000 for a meter loader to follow meter maids around.<p>--$10,000 for a huge stereo television and a laser-disc player.<p>--$10,000 for discs of movies directed by Albert Brooks, Michael Ritchie, Martin Scorsese, and others.<p>--$20,000 to bribe those directors to come over and "gossip as we watch their movies together."<p>DOUG E. DOUG<p>--$40,000 as a down payment on a house in Ocho Rios, Jamaica, for his mother. "After God comes Mom."<p>--$30,000 for antique jazz albums, every compact disc issued this month, and a box set of the Monkees, autographed by Mickey Dolenz, "whatever the expense."<p>--$4,010.50 for a trip to New York to see the Knicks. (The $10.50 is for two hot dogs and a soda.)<p>--$5,989.50 for antique clothes from American Rag Companie on La Brea in Los Angeles.<p>--$20,000 for the Children's Defense Fund.<p>JUDY TENUTA<p>--$20,000 to suck the fat out of Rush Limbaugh and turn him into a homeless shelter.<p>--$5,000 for Minoxidil treatments for Lyle and Erik Menendez.<p>--$30,000 to fly to London on the Concorde and give the Queen a complete makeover.<p>--$15,000 on Chunky Monkey ice cream, which would be force-fed to Cher so she'd blimp out and never appear on TV infomercials again.<p>--$30,000 to arrange for Lorena Bobbitt to spend one night with Joey Buttafuoco "and my ex-pig."<p> <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
