					<font size=4>
						 <p>
Tax exemption has finally come to the Church of Scientology. This doesn't just mean vindication for L. Ron Hubbard fans; it allows the cult's top-bracket types--Tom Cruise, John Travolta, Priscilla Presley--to claim new tax deductions. A guide to their potential savings:<p> On a 12-hour, $4,000 counseling course: $1,584
 On a $2,000 lifetime membership: $792
 On a $10,000 donation: $3,960
 On a $3,080 Hubbard E-Meter: $0 (not deductible)
