<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 94/01-100 Grand</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>94/01-100 Grand</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 <p>The challenge: Spend a tax-free windfall of $100,000--imaginary, we're afraid--on at least five items. Our players this month are three very different citizens of the world of style: Josie Natori, Phillippine-born Wall Streeter turned lingerie designer; Sorbonne-educated menswear designer Joseph Abboud, who specializes in understated, tactile clothing; and Kenneth Jay Lane, the flamboyant jewelry designer and habitue of the QVC shopping network.<p>
"If I can't buy just one drop-dead piece of jewelry from Jar ..."<p> $15,000 on a golfing trip to Scotland for her husband, Kenneth.<p> $30,000 on a Christmas trip to Paris for the ten members of her family who live in New York. "Our Paris apartment sleeps six; everyone else will stay in a hotel."<p> $30,000 to hire "a 'wife' for one year to organize my house."<p> $20,000 for a tour on the Orient Express for her and her husband.<p> $5,000 on Christmas decorations by Moulie-Savart.<p>Joseph Abboud<p> $14,000 on first-class tickets to Tokyo for him and wife Lynn.<p> $49,000 for a week in the best suite at the Imperial.<p> $25,000 to spend along the Ginza.<p> $10,000 for a Mikimoto necklace.<p> $2,000 for romantic dinners at Ginza Benkei in downtown Tokyo and Chinzan-So, a 20-acre garden restaurant.<p><p>Kenneth Jay Lane<p> $50,000 for a secret bird sanctuary in France, where a gamekeeper will shoot thrushes, doves, and ortolans "for my pleasure and gluttony when I'm in Paris." <p> $20,000 on account at Christie's "for when I next get carried away."<p> $1,000 to the Morgan Library "for lowering their wall as I asked."<p> $10,000 into a retirement fund for a few employees. "They know who they are."<p> $19,000 for upkeep of Jeff, his pet. ("Don't ask, 'Pet what?'")
 <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td width=390>
	
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  
		<a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  
