	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>93/11-The Next Big Thing</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						<p>Just think:If you had known Seattle was going to be hot, you could have invested early in coffee futures. If you had known Miami was next, you could have poured money into stucco. So that you don't miss the next wave, we asked some experts (sort of)to predict the next happening place.
Expert:Andrei Codrescu, 
commentator on National Public Radio and author of Road Scholar.
Next big city: New Orleans.
Why: "Mansions for next to nothing and a mega-casino that'll attract vultures from all over the East Coast."
Worth says:Buy Delta Queen Steamboat shares.
Experts:Andres Duany and Elizabeth Plater-Zyberk, Miami-based architects.
Next big city: Providence.
Why: Colleges, great public works, room for expansion. "And it doesn't have Harvard."
Worth says: Stock up on coffee syrup.
Expert:Tony Hiss, author of The Experience of Place.
Next big city:New York City is "two jumps away."
Why: Plans for a new rapid transit system, new approaches to the city's water supply.
Worth says: Lease a luxury box at Yankee Stadium.
Expert:Larry King, talk show host.
Next big city:Baltimore.
Why: Old meets new, best ballpark in America, great ethnic mix, progressive mayor.
Worth says:Pounce if Ulman Sports International, a lacrosse-gear company, goes public.
Expert:Let's Go, semi-hip travel guide published by Harvard students.
Next big city:Halifax, Nova Scotia.
why: University town, great transportation, rural options nearby, hot music scene.
Worth says:Buy into a donair franchise__spicy beef on pitas.<p><p>

					</font>
