						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 November 1993
Worth magazine/Outfront<p>GET USED TO IT<p>Progressive Asset Management judges companies on gay and lesbian issues, evaluating companies in five areas including partner benefits and support for HIV-positive employees. <a name="NASD:MSFT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14120"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Microsoft</b></a>, RJR Nabisco, and <a name="NYSE:HDI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10706"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Harley-Davidson</b></a> are among those that do well, but some well-known names fail the "lavender screen":<p>
- <a name="NYSE:BUD"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10116"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Anheuser-Busch</b></a><p>- <a name="NYSE:KMT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10849"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Kmart</b></a><p>- <a name="NYSE:MOB"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11006"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Mobil</b></a><p>- <a name="NYSE:PEP"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=11166"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>PepsiCo</b></a><p><p>

