					<font size=4>
						<p>The challenge: Spend a tax-free windfall of $100,000__imaginary, we're afraid__on at least five items. Our player for November is Christina Ricci, the smart 12-year-old actress who has appeared in Mermaids, The Hard Way, and The Addams Family. She reprises her ooky role as Wednesday in this month's Addams Family Values.<p>- $10,000 for family to visit relatives in Tuscany and Ireland__and to see Wales, because she loved Roald Dahl's Boy.<p>- $500 to bribe her way backstage at a Red Hot Chili Peppers concert.<p>- $30,000 for a yacht "to motor around in."<p>- $20,000 for two quarter horses (one for her sister).<p>- $500 for exercise machines__"especially that slide one on TV. You know:'Slide, slide, slide your way to shapely hips and thighs.'" <p>- $20,000 for AIDS research and patient care.<p>- $19,000 for high-octane computers like the ones that generated special effects for Addams Family Values. <p><p><p>

