	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 97/02-Need To Know: Asset Allocation</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/02-Need To Know: Asset Allocation</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						All's Quiet<p>
It's back to automatic pilot this month. Last month, two banks in our survey made sizable changes in their portfolio mix. This month, three banks stand pat. Only Bessemer Trust tinkers with its portfolio, increasing domestic and international equities by less than three percentage points each, while cutting cash by 3.6 points.<p>
BROWN BROTHERS<br>
Domestic Stocks (Russell 3000): 56%<br>
Domestic Bonds (Lehman Gov't/Corp.): 25%<br>
International Stocks (Morgan Stanley EAFE): 14%<br>
Cash (Ryan Labs): 5%<br>
<br>
NORTHERN TRUST<br>
Domestic Stocks: 72%<br>
International Stocks: 13%<br>
Domestic Stocks: 8%<br>
Cash: 5%<br>
Internationsl Bonds (J.P. Morgan Global): 2%<br>
<br>
BESSEMER TRUST<br>
Domestic Stocks: 51.7%<br>
International Stocks: 21.4%<br>
Domestic Bonds: 20.6%<br>
Cash: 6.3%<br>
<br>
UBS<br>
Domestic Stocks: 35%<br>
Domestic Bonds: 35%<br>
International Stocks: 20%<br>
Cash: 10%<br>
<br>
Recommended portfolios for an individual seeking long-term growth and total return.
					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
