Kemper Tax-Free Money Fund, 800-621-1048, 3.30<BR>
Fidelity Spartan Municipal Money Fund, 800-544-8888, 3.26<BR>
<BR>
Data as of 12/17/96. Sources: IBC Financial Data (<a HREF="http://www.ibcdata.com">www.ibcdata.com</A>) and BanxQuote (<a HREF="http://www.banx.com">www.banx.com</A>).
<BR><p>
**Saving for a Goal Two to Three Years Away
Our picks with an emphasis on safety and yield<p>
The ten funds below offer the best performance based on 12-month yield and three-year total return. We exclude candidates that had a loss of more than 3 percent during any three-month period in the past five years. The top-producing taxable and tax-exempt funds on our list have recently moved to boost yields by buying lower-quality bonds. Strong Short-Term Bond has 57 percent of its assets in bonds rated BBB or lower. USAA Tax-Exempt Short-Term Fund has 23 percent of its portfolio in BBB or lower bonds. This strategy can add risk, although both funds have histories of low volatility. Both also continue to maintain an average credit quality of A.
<BR>
TAXABLE<BR>
Fund, Telephone Number, Yield, 3-Year Total Return<BR>
Strong Short-Term Bond, 800-368-1030, 6.90%, 5.49%<BR>
Fidelity Mortgage Securities, 800-544-8888, 6.52, 8.00<BR>
Sit U.S. Government Securities, 800-332-5580, 6.23, 6.06<BR>
Strong Advantage, 800-368-1030, 6.08, 5.88<BR>
Vanguard Fixed-Income S-T Corporate, 800-662-7447, 6.00, 5.65<BR>
<BR>
TAX-FREE<BR>
