				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>97/01-10 Stocks to Avoid/Consider</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						10 STOCKS TO AVOID
Wayne Archambo manages $260 million worth of stock in small- and mid-sized companies for Boston Partners Asset Management, a firm that oversees a total of $6 billion for institutional investors. Archambo, a value investor, looks for companies that have solid balance sheets, are reasonably priced, and possess an "identifiable catalyst" that will cause earnings to rise in six to nine months. Archambo's portfolios have outperformed the Standard & Poor's 500 Stock Index by more than five percentage points since their inception in mid-1995. In Archambo's view, the market is full of stocks supported by unrealistic earnings expectations. As a result, companies that report even slightly disappointing earnings get pummeled. Especially overvalued, in his view, are the shares of Chesapeake Energy, which sells at 14 times annual cash flow while its gas-exploration peers sell at only 9 times cash flow. Competitors can easily start new driving ranges, he says, yet Family Golf Centers sells for 30 times earnings. Net profit margins at software maker PeopleSoft, which sports a price-to-earnings ratio of 68, have slipped from 13 percent at year-end 1995 to 12 percent in the first half of 1996. <p>
Company (EXCHANGE: TICKER) Fair Value (Anything over this price is too expensive).<br>
* Reasons<br>
<a name="NASD:BOST"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16244"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Boston Chicken</b></a> (Nasdaq: BOST) $26<br>
* Overstated earnings<br>
* 60 percent of assets are loans<br>
* Book value may be overstated<br>
<a name="NYSE:CHK"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=12049"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Chesapeake Energy</b></a> (NYSE: CHK) $25<br>
* Priced at four times cost of replacing oil and gas reserves <br>
* Aggressive reserve valuations <br>
<a name="NASD:CTYS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=47819"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Cityscape Financial</b></a> (Nasdaq: CTYS) $17<br>
* Sells at 8.5 times book value<br>
* Aggressive loans in U.K.    <br>
* Under-reserved for loan losses<br>  
<a name="NASD:CYRX"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16430"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Cyrix</b></a> (Nasdaq: CYRX) $12<br>
* Swelling inventories <br>
* Onetime boosts to income<br>
